title: Camille Pissarro Woman Bathing Her Feet in a Brook Matted Print
description:
Print developed from Camille Pissarro’s Woman Bathing Her Feet in a Brook, 1894, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Camille Pissarro referred to this painting in a letter of November 1894, when he wrote to his son Lucien that he wanted to send him a picture of “a little peasant girl dipping her feet in the water.” At the time, he considered the work almost finished but still lacking “that little something,” exclaiming optimistically, “I think I will get it, I feel it!”
  • Print Reproduction
  • Image Dimensions:  10.5 x 13.5 in.
  • Full Dimensions:  16 x 19 in.
  • Materials:  Premium cardstock.
